Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.5 × its height (
Fig. 4D
); pronope deep and medium-sized, side of pronotum largely smooth except some indistinct crenulae present medio-anteriorly and posteriorly (
Fig. 4D
); mesoscutum with lateral carina in front of tegulae present; epicnemial area largely crenulated; precoxal sulcus long and widely crenuate, almost reaching middle coxa; pleural sulcus crenulate; episternal scrobe round and deep; metapleuron reticulaterugose and with a round pit anteriorly (
